<html>

<!-- We can also add a StyleSheet Separately in the head tag under title tag , inside the link tag ( used to link external Style Sheets ) with attribute href which holds the value of the css file to be attached and attribute rel which holds the value of we prefer an external stylesheet type document
	-->
<head><title> adding css </title>
	<link href="style.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
	<h1 class="underline"> first header </h1>
	<div>
		<p class="underline"> First Paragraph </p>
		<p id="kulu"> Second </p>
		<p class="highlight"> Third G     </p>
	</div>
	<!-- A HTML Tag , for example p tag , Could Have multiple classes :
<p class ="multiple underline">dkjfhjdsf</p>
where , multiple is one Class and underline is another Class    -->
	<footer>
		<p> Fourth </p>
	</footer>

</body>
</html>




